CHAPTER-V
PROJECT ANALYSIS 

This internship was conducted as part of the MBA curriculum and aimed to bridge the gap between academic learning and practical industry exposure
 Duration and Location of the Internship
·	Internship Duration: 2 months
·	Start Date: 2 June, 2025
·	End Date:  31 july, 2025
·	Internship Location: Marketing and Development Research Associates, Delhi

 Objectives of the Project
  To compile, validate, and organize institutional data for the preparation of the 2025 B-School      Rankings.
  To strengthen the credibility of rankings through cross-verification of institutional claims with secondary sources.
  To improve data completeness and accuracy by coordinating with institutions via calls, emails, and follow-ups.
  To deliver a structured dataset aligned with the ranking methodology, supporting editorial and analytics teams.
  To gain practical exposure to market research methodologies and enhance skills in data management, analysis, and reporting.

                                                                                  11
 Scope of the Project
The project covered over 100 business schools and universities across India, focusing on  multiple ranking parameters such as infrastructure, faculty strength, placements, accreditations, international collaborations, and ROI trends.
Included both primary outreach (emails, calls, follow-ups) and secondary research (websites, brochures, accreditation databases).
Scope was limited to data collection, cleaning, validation, and structuring; final ranking decisions rested with senior editorial and analytics teams.
The project directly contributed to the India Today–MDRA 2025 Rankings publication.

Conceptual Framework
The project was based on the principle that accurate and credible data is the foundation of meaningful rankings. The framework combined:
Data Collection → Gathering raw information from institutions and public sources.
Data Validation → Cross-checking claims with independent databases and accreditation bodies.
Data Structuring → Standardizing and categorizing data into ranking parameters.
Data Reporting → Organizing datasets for editorial teams and preparing executive insights.
This framework ensured that the research outcomes were methodologically sound, transparent, and credible.

Research Methodology
1. Research Design
Approach: Combination of secondary research and institutional outreach (primary data).
Design: Descriptive and analytical in nature, aimed at organizing educational institutions into a comparative ranking framework.
Data Sources: Institutional websites, brochures, email responses, telephonic follow-ups, accreditation bodies, and independent public databases
 Methodology Description
Identification of Institutions: Selected based on previous year’s rankings and current academic reputation.

                                                                         12
Data Compilation: Collected raw data manually from websites, brochures, and direct communication.
Data Cleaning: Removed duplicates, standardized entries (fees, course names, locations), and used Excel functions (=TRIM(), =CLEAN(), =PROPER()).
Data Validation: Cross-verified information (placements, accreditations, collaborations) with secondary sources.
Data Enrichment: Supplemented missing inputs through follow-ups and verified public data.
Data Structuring: Segregated institutions by type, specialization, and geography; created profiles and index sheets.
Final Deliverables: Prepared structured Excel datasets with filters, legends, and notes; created executive summaries highlighting trends.

 Detailed Work Responsibilities
My work primarily involved compiling and recording institutional data from emails, brochures, and official websites, followed by cleaning, standardizing, and formatting large datasets in Excel. I actively reached out to institutions through emails, calls, and follow-ups to gather missing information and ensured accuracy by cross-verifying institutional claims with accreditation databases and independent reports. Additionally, I categorized institutions and prepared individual profiles aligned with ranking parameters, while also developing executive summaries and briefs for senior editors and research leads. Finally, I contributed to the preparation of the comprehensive dataset for the 2025 rankings publication.

  Tools, Platforms, and Channels Used
extensively worked with MS Excel for data entry, cleaning, formatting, and creating pivot tables, charts, and summaries. Using MS Word, I drafted summaries, notes, and reports to support research documentation. For institutional outreach and follow-ups, I managed email communication through Outlook and Gmail, while also conducting telephonic calls for direct interaction with academic representatives. Additionally, I utilized web browsers and PDF documents to extract secondary data from official websites, brochures, and accreditation reports. To ensure consistency and alignment with ranking parameters, I also worked with internal pre-formatted Excel templates for indexing and data organization.

