CHAPTER-VI PROJECT WISE ANALYSIS
 Phase 1:Project Planning and Orientation
•	Understood the objective of the B-School Ranking Project and familiarized with MDRA’s methodology.
•	Reviewed previous year’s datasets and ranking frameworks.
•	Identified key parameters such as infrastructure, placements, accreditations, ROI, and international exposure.
•	Prepared initial plan for data collection, validation, and communication strategy.
Phase 2: Data Collection
•	Conducted secondary research by visiting institutional websites, brochures, accreditation portals, and public reports.
•	Engaged in primary data collection through outreach to institutions via emails and telephonic calls.
•	Collected data related to academic programs, placement records, faculty profiles, infrastructure, and student outcomes.
•	Created raw data sheets in MS Excel with institution-wise entries.
Phase 3: Data Cleaning and Validation
•	Standardized the collected data to ensure consistency in format (fees, course titles, location codes).
•	Applied Excel functions like TRIM, CLEAN, VLOOKUP, and Pivot Tables to organize data.
•	Cross-verified claims (placement figures, accreditations, collaborations) using independent sources and official records.
•	Eliminated duplicate and inconsistent entries for a reliable dataset.

                                                                                15


Phase 4: Data Structuring and Categorization
•	Segregated institutions based on type (government/private), region, specialization, and accreditations.
•	Prepared institutional profiles including highlights of academic strengths and placement records.
•	Structured the dataset in alignment with ranking parameters to simplify analysis for senior teams.
•	Created index sheets and legends for easier navigation within the dataset.

Phase 5: Institutional Interaction and Follow-Ups
•	Directly interacted with placement officers, faculty coordinators, and administrative staff for authentic information.
•	Sent structured queries via emails to clarify discrepancies.
•	Followed up with institutions through calls to collect missing or incomplete data.
•	Maintained communication logs for accountability and transparency.

Phase 6: Report Preparation and Deliverables
•	Compiled data into Excel dashboards with filtering and sorting features.
•	Prepared executive summaries highlighting market trends, institutional performance, and emerging patterns.
•	Contributed insights to the editorial team for the India Today–MDRA B-School Rankings.
