                                                                                  17
CHAPTER-VII
SUMMARY OF PROJECT ANALYSYS AND FINDINGS

Introduction
The Summer Internship Project focused on market research and data compilation for India Today–MDRA B-School Rankings 2025. The primary objective was to build a comprehensive, credible, and structured database of Indian B-Schools by collecting, cleaning, validating, and organizing data from both primary and secondary sources.
The project scope covered 100+ institutions across India and involved multiple stages: data collection from official websites, brochures, and direct outreach; cleaning and standardizing datasets using Excel functions; verifying institutional claims through cross-checking with accreditation bodies and credible public data; and preparing structured profiles and summaries aligned with ranking parameters.
The research methodology combined primary data (emails, telephonic follow-ups, and institutional responses) with secondary research (archived reports, PDFs, and websites). Tools such as MS Excel and MS Word were extensively used for data management, formatting, pivot tables, charting, and report writing. Communication channels included emails, calls, and professional correspondence, which enhanced interpersonal and stakeholder engagement skills.
Throughout the project, significant challenges included incomplete institutional responses, inconsistent data formats, and time-bound validation requirements. These were addressed through persistent follow-ups, careful standardization, and structured reporting practices.
The analysis revealed several key findings:
•	Data Reliability Improves Through Verification: Many institutions overstated achievements in placements or infrastructure, which required independent validation.
•	Sectoral Patterns Identified: Trends in ROI, accreditations, and geographical distribution of top B-Schools were observed.
                                                                  18
•	Standardization is Critical: Uniformity in data (e.g., fees, faculty count, locations) enhanced comparability and usability for rankings.
•	Holistic Datasets Add Value: Incorporating additional parameters like international collaborations and infrastructure improved the ranking framework.
•	Professional Communication is Essential: Effective outreach and polite follow-ups directly impacted data completeness and credibility.
Ultimately, the project resulted in a well-structured, validated dataset that directly contributed to the 2025 B-School Rankings publication. It also provided hands-on exposure to real-world research processes, strengthened skills in data analytics and reporting, and demonstrated how structured research underpins credible rankings in the education sector.


