Introduction
The Summer Internship Project at MDRA offered a unique opportunity to gain first-hand exposure to the field of market research and academic rankings. The project allowed me to engage in diverse activities such as data collection, validation, structuring, and reporting, while also interacting with institutional representatives, research teams, and editorial staff. This experience significantly contributed to my professional, technical, and personal development.
This chapter presents my personal reflections and key learnings gained during the course of the internship.
